==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prate
<hw>Prate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Prated</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Prating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Akin to LG. & D.
<ets>praten</ets>, Dan. <ets>prate</ets>, Sw. & Icel.
<ets>prata</ets>.]</ety> <def>To talk much and to little purpose; to be
loquacious; to speak foolishly; to babble.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To <qex>prate</qex> and talk for life and honor.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And make a fool presume to <qex>prate</qex> of love.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Prate
<hw>Prate</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To utter foolishly; to speak
without reason or purpose; to chatter, or babble.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What nonsense would the fool, thy master, <qex>prate</qex>,⟦br⟧
When thou, his knave, canst talk at such a rate !</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Prate
<hw>Prate</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Akin to LG. & D. <ets>praat</ets>,
Sw. <ets>prat</ets>.]</ety> <def>Talk to little purpose; trifling talk;
unmeaning loquacity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sick of tops, and poetry, and <qex>prate</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Pope.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prateful</ent>⟦br⟧
